10 Maladetta sie tu, antica lupa, 11 che più che tutte l’altre bestie hai preda 12 per la tua fame sanza fine cupa!
13 O ciel, nel cui girar par che si creda 14 le condizion di qua giù trasmutarsi, 15 quando verrà per cui questa disceda?
16 Noi andavam con passi lenti e scarsi, 17 e io attento a l’ombre, ch’i’ sentia 18 pietosamente piangere e lagnarsi;
19 e per ventura udi’ «Dolce Maria!» 20 dinanzi a noi chiamar così nel pianto 21 come fa donna che in parturir sia;
22 e seguitar: «Povera fosti tanto, 23 quanto veder si può per quello ospizio 24 dove sponesti il tuo portato santo».

query.result:
**English:**
10 Accursed be you, ancient she-wolf, 11 who more than all other beasts have prey, 12 for your insatiable hunger!
13 O heavens, in whose revolution it seems to be believed 14 that the conditions down here can be changed, 15 when will he come for whom this [she-wolf] will depart?
16 We were going with slow and weary steps, 17 and I was paying attention to the shades, whom I heard 18 piteously weeping and wailing;
19 and by chance I heard "Sweet Mary!" 20 being called out before us in the weeping 21 as a woman does who is in labor;
22 and then: "You were so poor, 23 as can be seen from that inn 24 where you gave birth to your holy burden."
**Sanskrit:**
10 Śaptā tvam asi, purāṇī vṛkā, 11 yā sarvāṇi anyāni paśūn adhikaṃ bhakṣayasi 12 tava anantaṃ kṣudhāyāḥ kuṭilaṃ gahanam!
13 O dyauḥ, yasya parivartane manyate 14 ihāvartamānāni sthitīni vikurvāṇīti, 15 kadaṃ bhaviṣyati sa yasya nimittam ayam gamiṣyati?
16 Vayam agacchamaḥ mandaiḥ kṣīṇaiḥ ca padaiḥ, 17 aham ca śraddadhānaḥ chāyāsu, yāḥ aham aśṛṇvam 18 karuṇayā rudantīḥ ca vilāpantīś ca;
19 tataś ca adṛṣṭena śuśrāva "Svāhā Marīce!" 20 asmākam agre evam ākrāśamānam rodane 21 yathā karoti strī prasūtau sthitā;
22 tataś ca anvadhāvat: "Daridrā āsīḥ tvam atiśayam, 23 yathā draṣṭum śakyate tena ātithyaśālāt 24 yatra tvam nyadadhāḥ tava bhāram pavitram."

